1
00:00:07,542 --> 00:00:08,834
- EARTH.

2
00:00:08,875 --> 00:00:10,458
FIRE.

3
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:12,125
AIR.

4
00:00:12,166 --> 00:00:14,500
WATER.

5
00:00:14,542 --> 00:00:18,375
ONLY THE AVATAR CAN MASTER
ALL FOUR ELEMENTS

6
00:00:18,417 --> 00:00:21,083
AND BRING BALANCE
TO THE WORLD.

7
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:24,041
[dramatic music]

8
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:28,750
- THE AIR NATION IS REBORN!

9
00:00:28,792 --> 00:00:30,834
THANKS TO THE ENERGY SHIFT
DURING HARMONIC CONVERGENCE,

10
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:33,500
CERTAIN PEOPLE HAVE ACQUIRED
AIRBENDING ABILITIES,

11
00:00:33,542 --> 00:00:35,709
INCLUDING BUMI, KAI,
AND OPAL.

12
00:00:35,750 --> 00:00:38,333
BUT ALTHOUGH THE NEW RECRUITS
SHOW A LOT OF PROMISE,

13
00:00:38,375 --> 00:00:39,625
THEY STILL HAVE A LOT
TO LEARN.

14
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:42,250
SO WHILE KORRA REMAINS SAFE
IN ZAOFU,

15
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:43,917
TENZIN HAS BROUGHT
THE AIRBENDERS

16
00:00:43,959 --> 00:00:46,250
TO THE NORTHERN AIR TEMPLE
TO BEGIN THEIR TRAINING.

17
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:54,709
- HIS PUPILS ONCE AGAIN PLEADED
WITH THEIR MASTER

18
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:57,375
TO EAT SOMETHING,
BUT HE REFUSED,

19
00:00:57,417 --> 00:01:00,000
JUST LIKE HE HAD EACH DAY
THE ENTIRE SUMMER.

20
00:01:00,041 --> 00:01:02,625
INSTEAD, HE SIMPLY MEDITATED,

21
00:01:02,667 --> 00:01:05,375
GETTING HIS NOURISHMENT
FROM THE UNIVERSE.

22
00:01:05,417 --> 00:01:09,208
SO MONK TANG XU COMPLETED
THE 97TH DAY

23
00:01:09,250 --> 00:01:11,083
OF HIS HISTORIC FAST

24
00:01:11,125 --> 00:01:13,750
ON WHICH ISLAND?

25
00:01:13,792 --> 00:01:14,834
- OOH! OOH, OOH!

26
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:17,083
- ANYONE BESIDES OTAKU,

27
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:20,000
WHO ALREADY STUDIED THIS
IN HIS ACOLYTE TRAINING...

28
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:21,291
- OOH, OOH, OOH!

29
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:22,250
- AND IS ANSWERING
EVERY QUESTION?

30
00:01:22,291 --> 00:01:25,208
- OOH! OOH! OOH!

31
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:26,542
WHALETAIL ISLAND!

32
00:01:26,583 --> 00:01:30,000
- THAT IS CORRECT.
AGAIN.

33
00:01:30,041 --> 00:01:31,625
NOW, ON DAY 98--

34
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:34,709
[laughter]

35
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:36,625
- [squeaky voice]
GREETINGS, AIR PEOPLE.

36
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:40,458
I COME SEEKING BORING STORIES
TO TAKE BACK TO THE SPIRIT
WORLD.

37
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,083
[shouts]

38
00:01:42,125 --> 00:01:44,208
[laughter]

39
00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:48,000
- [clears throat]

40
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:51,000
[inspiring music]

41
00:01:51,041 --> 00:01:58,333
♪ ♪

42
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,458
- THAT WAS INCREDIBLE!

43
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,875
WHEN DO WE GET TO FLY AROUND
ON OUR OWN BISON LIKE THAT?

44
00:02:07,917 --> 00:02:09,542
- ONLY AFTER MANY YEARS
OF PRACTICE

45
00:02:09,583 --> 00:02:11,083
AND INTENSE TRAINING.

46
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:12,875
[students groaning]

47
00:02:12,917 --> 00:02:15,583
BESIDES, WE DON'T HAVE ENOUGH
BISON HERE FOR ALL OF YOU.

48
00:02:15,625 --> 00:02:18,458
- WHAT ABOUT THOSE?
IT'S A WHOLE HERD OF BISONS.

49
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,750
- ACTUALLY, THE PLURAL
OF "BISON" IS "BISON."

50
00:02:20,792 --> 00:02:22,041
- [laughs]
WHOA!

51
00:02:22,083 --> 00:02:24,208
- COOL!
- WOW, LOOK AT THAT.

52
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:27,208
- CAN WE RIDE THOSE?
- NO, THAT'S A WILD HERD.

53
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:30,041
IT WOULD TAKE MANY YEARS
TO TAME THEM.

54
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:31,792
NOW LET'S GET BACK
TO OUR LESSONS.

55
00:02:31,834 --> 00:02:33,291
- DAD!

56
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:35,000
WE BROUGHT YOU
MORE AIRBENDERS!

57
00:02:35,041 --> 00:02:36,959
[bison grunting]

58
00:02:40,709 --> 00:02:42,417
- OKAY, EVERYONE IS DISMISSED.

59
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:45,125
WE'LL JUST
PICK THIS UP...

60
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:46,834
[sighs]
TOMORROW.

61
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:52,000
HOW WAS EVERYTHING
IN THE CITY?

62
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:54,083
- WELL, WE HAD A LITTLE SCARE,

63
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:55,500
BUT EVERYTHING IS OKAY.

64
00:02:55,542 --> 00:02:57,458
ZAHEER INFILTRATED
THE AIR TEMPLE.

65
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:59,291
- WHAT?
IS EVERYONE ALL RIGHT?

66
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:00,959
- EVERYONE'S FINE.

67
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,959
I FOUGHT WITH HIM,
BUT HE GOT AWAY.

68
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,125
AND HE STOLE SOME OLD NECKLACE
THAT HAD SOMETHING TO DO

69
00:03:05,166 --> 00:03:08,250
WITH GURU LAK...SCHMEER.

70
00:03:08,291 --> 00:03:09,667
- GURU LAGHIMA.

71
00:03:09,709 --> 00:03:11,709
- RIGHT.

72
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:13,792
YOU KNOW, I CAN NEVER KEEP
ALL THOSE GURUS STRAIGHT.

73
00:03:13,834 --> 00:03:15,750
THERE WERE, LIKE,
A MILLION OF THEM.

74
00:03:15,792 --> 00:03:17,583
REMEMBER THAT LONG, BORING STORY
ABOUT THE GUY

75
00:03:17,625 --> 00:03:18,917
WHO NEVER ATE?

76
00:03:18,959 --> 00:03:21,250
- YES, I REMEMBER.

77
00:03:21,291 --> 00:03:23,917
- AVATAR KORRA IS CALLING
ON THE TEMPLE RADIO.

78
00:03:23,959 --> 00:03:26,542
[static]

79
00:03:26,583 --> 00:03:28,500
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
WHERE ARE YOU?

80
00:03:28,542 --> 00:03:30,166
- WITH BEIFONG'S SISTER
IN ZAOFU.

81
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:32,250
WE'RE TOTALLY SAFE,
UNLESS WE GET CAUGHT

82
00:03:32,291 --> 00:03:34,542
IN ANOTHER FIGHT
BETWEEN SU AND LIN.

83
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:36,083
- LIN WILLINGLY TOOK YOU
TO HER SISTER?

84
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:37,542
- NOT EXACTLY.

85
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,625
WE GOT A CALL
ABOUT A NEW AIRBENDER,

86
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:41,417
AND IT TURNED OUT TO BE
SU'S DAUGHTER, OPAL.

87
00:03:41,458 --> 00:03:43,208
SHE'LL BE HEADED
YOUR WAY SOON.

88
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,542
- REALLY?
THAT'S WONDERFUL!

89
00:03:44,583 --> 00:03:46,959
- SHE IS WONDERFUL

90
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,333
AND PRETTY
AND SO SMART!

91
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:52,834
AND SHE SMELLS LIKE FLOWERS.

92
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:53,959
SORRY.

93
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,834
BOLIN OUT.

94
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,208
- HOW'S THE TRAINING GOING?

95
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:59,208
- NOT SO WELL, I'M AFRAID.

96
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,667
NO ONE SEEMS TO BE INTERESTED
IN THE HARD WORK

97
00:04:01,709 --> 00:04:04,375
REQUIRED TO BECOME A PART
OF THE AIR NATION.

98
00:04:04,417 --> 00:04:06,458
- YOU NEED TO GIVE YOURSELF
A BREAK.

99
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:08,917
LET JINORA AND THE KIDS
HELP YOU OUT.

100
00:04:08,959 --> 00:04:11,041
AND WHAT ABOUT BUMI?
HE WAS A NAVAL COMMANDER.

101
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:12,333
MAYBE HE HAS SOME IDEAS

102
00:04:12,375 --> 00:04:13,625
ABOUT HOW TO GET PEOPLE
MOTIVATED.

103
00:04:13,667 --> 00:04:16,125
- BUMI?
HE'S MY WORST STUDENT!

104
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:18,875
- YEAH, BUT HE LOVES
TO ORGANIZE PEOPLE.

105
00:04:18,917 --> 00:04:20,917
IF YOU ASK HIM FOR HELP,
YOU CAN TRICK HIM

106
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:22,750
INTO TAKING
MORE RESPONSIBILITY

107
00:04:22,792 --> 00:04:25,208
BY MAKING HIM THINK
THE WHOLE THING WAS HIS IDEA.

108
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:26,709
- HMM.

109
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,083
THAT ACTUALLY SOUNDS
LIKE A GOOD PLAN.

110
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:32,667
YOU'RE TURNING INTO
A PRETTY WISE AVATAR AFTER ALL.

111
00:04:32,709 --> 00:04:36,417
- CONFLICT RESOLUTION.
IT'S WHAT I DO.

112
00:04:36,458 --> 00:04:37,875
- WE SHOULD GO DOWN THERE.

113
00:04:37,917 --> 00:04:39,750
I WANT TO FLY
ONE OF THOSE BISONS.

114
00:04:39,792 --> 00:04:41,917
- I DON'T KNOW.
WE MIGHT GET IN TROUBLE.

115
00:04:41,959 --> 00:04:43,917
- COME ON,
LET'S HAVE SOME FUN.

116
00:04:43,959 --> 00:04:46,208
WE'LL BE BACK BEFORE ANYONE
REALIZES WE'RE GONE.

117
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:47,875
- I GUESS IT WILL BE
ALL RIGHT.

118
00:04:47,917 --> 00:04:50,875
[exciting music]

119
00:04:50,917 --> 00:04:58,917
♪ ♪

120
00:05:02,291 --> 00:05:03,834
- LOOK, BABY BISONS.

121
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:05,834
HOW COME THEY'RE ALL
ON THE GROUND?

122
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:07,542
- AIR BISON CALVES CAN'T FLY
FOR A WEEK OR TWO

123
00:05:07,583 --> 00:05:09,041
AFTER THEY'RE BORN,

124
00:05:09,083 --> 00:05:10,417
SO THE ENTIRE HERD WILL STAY
NEAR THE GROUND

125
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:11,750
IN THE VALLEY.

126
00:05:11,792 --> 00:05:13,375
- LET'S GO SEE THE BABIES.

127
00:05:13,417 --> 00:05:15,959
- BE CAREFUL.
THE MOTHERS ARE VERY PROTECTIVE.

128
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,291
[bison growling softly]

129
00:05:23,417 --> 00:05:25,417
- AW, LOOK HOW CUTE.

130
00:05:25,458 --> 00:05:28,458
- KAI, GET OUT OF THERE!

131
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,166
[bison growling aggressively]

132
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:36,208
[suspenseful music]

133
00:05:36,250 --> 00:05:38,166
♪ ♪

134
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:39,667
- WHOA!

135
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:45,834
WOW, YOU REALLY SAVED ME
DOWN THERE.
- OH.
- YOU KNOW,

136
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:47,458
YOU'RE
AN INCREDIBLE AIRBENDER.

137
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:49,625
- WELL, I'VE BEEN TRAINING
FOR A LONG TIME.

138
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:52,667
- THEN WHY DON'T YOU HAVE
TATTOOS LIKE AN AIRBENDING
MASTER?

139
00:05:52,709 --> 00:05:54,667
- MY DAD SAYS
I'M NOT A MASTER YET.

140
00:05:54,709 --> 00:05:56,834
- YOU CAN DO EVERYTHING
YOUR DAD CAN,

141
00:05:56,875 --> 00:05:59,208
PLUS YOU HAVE
ALL THOSE SPIRIT-Y POWERS.

142
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:03,000
IF ANYONE'S A MASTER,
YOU ARE.

143
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,333
- [chuckles]
SO WE BRING THE NET DOWN

144
00:06:05,375 --> 00:06:08,250
ON THE HEAD PIRATE,
AND HE LOOKS AROUND REAL SAD

145
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,041
AND SAYS, "I KNEW I SHOULD HAVE
FOLLOWED MY DREAMS

146
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:12,417
AND BECOME A DENTIST."

147
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:13,917
- [laughs]

148
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:15,709
HOW COME YOU GREW UP
TO BE SO COOL,

149
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,542
WHILE TENZIN BECAME
SUCH A STICK IN THE MUD?

150
00:06:18,583 --> 00:06:21,500
- WELL, I GUESS "COOL" IS
JUST SOMETHING YOU'RE BORN WITH.

151
00:06:21,542 --> 00:06:23,166
- BUMI, CAN I TALK TO YOU?

152
00:06:25,792 --> 00:06:28,125
- LET ME GUESS--YOU WANT
TO CRITICIZE ME FOR SOMETHING.

153
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,417
- ACTUALLY, I NEED YOUR HELP.

154
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:31,834
- OH, YEAH?
WITH WHAT?

155
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:33,166
- I DON'T THINK
I'M DOING VERY WELL

156
00:06:33,208 --> 00:06:34,834
WITH THE NEW AIRBENDERS,

157
00:06:34,875 --> 00:06:37,625
AND EVERYONE KNOWS
YOU'RE A NATURAL LEADER.

158
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:39,917
- TRUE, I DID WIN
THE ADMIRAL TUNG

159
00:06:39,959 --> 00:06:44,166
NATURAL LEADERSHIP AWARD
TWICE.

160
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:47,000
- WHAT WOULD YOU DO
IF YOU WERE IN CHARGE?

161
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:49,250
HELP ME BE MORE LIKE YOU.

162
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:51,792
- I'D LOVE TO.

163
00:06:51,834 --> 00:06:53,291
YOU'VE GOTTA USE
MILITARY DISCIPLINE

164
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,250
TO WHIP THESE TROOPS
INTO SHAPE.

165
00:06:55,291 --> 00:06:57,125
THE ONLY WAY TO DEAL
WITH NEW RECRUITS

166
00:06:57,166 --> 00:07:00,417
IS TO BREAK THEM DOWN,
SO YOU CAN BUILD THEM BACK UP.

167
00:07:00,458 --> 00:07:02,875
RULE WITH AN IRON FIST.

168
00:07:02,917 --> 00:07:05,500
SHOW THEM WHO THE MASTER IS.

169
00:07:05,542 --> 00:07:08,417
- THANKS FOR THE INSIGHT.
- MY PLEASURE.

170
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:15,417
[horn blares]

171
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:16,875
[students groaning]

172
00:07:16,917 --> 00:07:19,250
- DAWN PATROL!
EVERYONE UP!

173
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:21,250
- UGH.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

174
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:22,959
IT'S BARELY LIGHT OUT.

175
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,917
- I'M TAKING YOUR ADVICE.

176
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:27,083
I'M GOING TO BREAK YOU DOWN
AND BUILD YOU BACK UP.

177
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:28,709
NOW GET MOVING, RECRUIT!

178
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,417
- [groans]

179
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:36,041
[peaceful music]

180
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:41,208
♪ ♪

181
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:44,208
- [grunts]

182
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:46,250
- [grunts]
- [groans]

183
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:49,208
- NOTHING LIKE A 10-MILE HIKE
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

184
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:52,041
- DON'T THESE ROBES COME
IN A WARM, BISON FUR VERSION?

185
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:55,166
- NO, OF COURSE NOT!

186
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:56,583
- OH!

187
00:07:56,625 --> 00:07:58,208
IF IT WEREN'T SO COLD,

188
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:00,083
I'D GO RIGHT BACK TO SLEEP.

189
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:02,500
- THEN THIS IS THE PERFECT TIME
TO LEARN MEDITATION

190
00:08:02,542 --> 00:08:05,166
AND PROPER BREATHING TECHNIQUE.

191
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:06,875
AIRBENDERS ARE ABLE
TO WARM THEMSELVES

192
00:08:06,917 --> 00:08:08,792
WITH ONLY THEIR BREATHING.

193
00:08:08,834 --> 00:08:11,166
EVERYONE GET
INTO THE LOTUS POSITION.

194
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:14,000
AH, THIS IS SO MUCH MORE
REFRESHING THAN SLEEPING.

195
00:08:14,041 --> 00:08:16,625
- YOU KNOW, WHEN I SAID
THAT THING ABOUT AN IRON FIST--

196
00:08:16,667 --> 00:08:20,083
- HUSH.
MEDITATION TIME.

197
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,792
FOCUS.

198
00:08:35,917 --> 00:08:38,166
- CAN WE GO BACK TO BED NOW?

199
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:39,750
- NOW THAT WE'RE REFRESHED
AND LOOSE

200
00:08:39,792 --> 00:08:41,041
FROM OUR HIKE
AND MEDITATION,

201
00:08:41,083 --> 00:08:43,083
IT'S TIME
FOR A BALANCING EXERCISE.

202
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:46,291
[air whooshes]

203
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,750
THE KEY IS TO MAINTAIN YOUR
HEAVEN AND EARTH CONNECTION.

204
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:53,792
NOW YOU TRY.

205
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:56,000
[students grunting]
BACK ON THE POSTS!

206
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:57,750
IT'S NOT HARD
IF YOU CONCENTRATE!

207
00:08:57,792 --> 00:08:58,750
[all grunting]

208
00:08:58,792 --> 00:09:00,333
- WHOA.
- UGH.

209
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:01,875
WHOA!

210
00:09:01,917 --> 00:09:03,375
[grunts]

211
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:05,667
- GET BACK UP!

212
00:09:05,709 --> 00:09:07,667
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
YOU CAN'T HANDLE IT, SOLDIER?

213
00:09:07,709 --> 00:09:09,875
- [groans]

214
00:09:09,917 --> 00:09:12,208
[squeaking]

215
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:14,291
[students grunting]

216
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,500
- DON'T YOU THINK YOU'RE BEING
A LITTLE HARD ON THEM?

217
00:09:16,542 --> 00:09:18,834
- DON'T WORRY.
THEY CAN TAKE IT.

218
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:20,959
YOU'LL SEE.

219
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,291
IGNORE THE LEMURS
DIGGING IN YOUR EARS.

220
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:24,917
CONCENTRATE ON YOUR BREATHING,

221
00:09:24,959 --> 00:09:26,417
AND YOU WON'T EVEN KNOW
THEY'RE THERE.

222
00:09:26,458 --> 00:09:29,208
- WHOA, UH, UGH, OH!

223
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:34,500
- WHEN THE HEAD IS SHAVED,
AN AIRBENDER IS ABLE

224
00:09:34,542 --> 00:09:36,041
TO FEEL THE WIND AROUND HIM.

225
00:09:36,083 --> 00:09:40,125
IT IS BOTH HUMBLING
AND FREEING.

226
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,083
- HEY, YOU WANNA SNEAK AWAY

227
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:44,041
AND GO CHECK
ON THE BABY BISONS?

228
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:46,625
- SHH. YOU SHOULD BE
PAYING ATTENTION.

229
00:09:49,709 --> 00:09:51,250
[head squeaks]

230
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:52,875
- ALL RIGHT, WHO'S NEXT?

231
00:09:52,917 --> 00:09:54,792
- I'M NOT SURE I WANT
TO SHAVE MY HEAD.

232
00:09:54,834 --> 00:09:56,291
- THAT'S FINE.

233
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:57,917
SHAVING YOUR HEAD
IS A PERSONAL CHOICE.

234
00:09:57,959 --> 00:10:01,458
- WAIT, WHAT?
- ANYONE ELSE?

235
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,583
FINE, THEN WE CAN GET RIGHT
TO OUR NEXT TRAINING EXERCISE--

236
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:04,917
OBSTACLE COURSE!

237
00:10:04,959 --> 00:10:06,625
[students groan]

238
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,542
- YOU'RE PUSHING TOO HARD.

239
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:13,000
MAYBE WE SHOULD GIVE THEM
A BREAK.

240
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:16,709
- JINORA, I HAVE THIS
UNDER CONTROL.

241
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:21,709
[dramatic music]

242
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:23,208
♪ ♪

243
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:25,500
CONCENTRATE.

244
00:10:25,542 --> 00:10:30,125
REMEMBER, AIRBENDERS MOVE
LIKE THE WIND.

245
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:32,083
- AGH!

246
00:10:32,125 --> 00:10:35,959
♪ ♪

247
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,291
- UGH!

248
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,875
- [whimpers]

249
00:10:38,917 --> 00:10:42,125
♪ ♪

250
00:10:42,166 --> 00:10:43,709
- STAY LIGHT ON YOUR FEET,
AND YOU'LL NEVER FEEL

251
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:48,583
THE STINGING RASH-CACTUS.

252
00:10:48,625 --> 00:10:50,333
- [grunts]
- OW!

253
00:10:50,375 --> 00:10:57,125
♪ ♪

254
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:58,917
- [grunting]

255
00:11:01,875 --> 00:11:04,000
- EVERYONE IS WAITING
FOR YOU, BUMI.

256
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:05,875
IF YOU DON'T MAKE IT OVER
IN THE NEXT 30 SECONDS,

257
00:11:05,917 --> 00:11:08,000
THEY'LL ALL HAVE TO RUN
THROUGH THE COURSE AGAIN.

258
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:10,000
- YOU CAN DO IT, BUMI!
- COME ON!

259
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:13,208
- [grunting]

260
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,583
AGH!

261
00:11:14,625 --> 00:11:17,542
[grunting]

262
00:11:20,917 --> 00:11:22,583
- GET BACK ON THAT WALL,
RECRUIT!

263
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:24,250
YOU'RE LETTING
YOUR FELLOW AIRBENDERS DOWN.

264
00:11:24,291 --> 00:11:25,583
- [growls]

265
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:27,000
I'M FINISHED!

266
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:29,041
I NEVER WANTED
TO BE AN AIRBENDER,

267
00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:31,208
AND I'M TOO OLD TO BE
BACK IN BOOT CAMP!

268
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:33,250
COUNT ME OUT.

269
00:11:33,291 --> 00:11:34,667
- FINE, QUIT!

270
00:11:34,709 --> 00:11:37,250
WE DON'T NEED YOUR ATTITUDE
IN THE NEW AIR NATION.

271
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:39,125
- MASTER TENZIN?

272
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:41,667
WHEN DO WE GET TO GO HOME
AND VISIT OUR FAMILIES?

273
00:11:41,709 --> 00:11:44,041
- GO HOME?
YOU JUST GOT HERE.

274
00:11:44,083 --> 00:11:45,959
- WHEN'S DINNER?
I'M STARVING.

275
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,375
- CAN I CHANGE
OUT OF MY ROBE NOW?

276
00:11:47,417 --> 00:11:48,959
IT'S ITCHY.

277
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,208
- THIS IS JUST AS BAD
AS THE EARTH QUEEN'S PRISON.

278
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:52,959
- I'M TIRED
OF ALL THIS COMPLAINING.

279
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,041
JINORA, TAKE OVER.

280
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:57,667
- DOES THIS MEAN
I'M THE MASTER NOW?

281
00:11:57,709 --> 00:12:00,375
- YES. JUST LEAD THEM
THROUGH SOME BASIC EXERCISES.

282
00:12:00,417 --> 00:12:02,542
- WELL, SINCE I'M A MASTER,

283
00:12:02,583 --> 00:12:04,333
WHEN DO YOU THINK I CAN GET
MY TATTOOS?

284
00:12:04,375 --> 00:12:06,792
- WHAT BROUGHT THIS ON?
- I WAS JUST TALKING TO KAI,

285
00:12:06,834 --> 00:12:08,500
AND HE WAS ASKING ME, SO--

286
00:12:08,542 --> 00:12:10,333
- KAI! WHAT DOES HE KNOW
ABOUT WHEN

287
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:12,041
YOU SHOULD GET TATTOOS?

288
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:13,917
THE ANSWER IS NO!
YOU'RE JUST A LITTLE GIRL.

289
00:12:13,959 --> 00:12:15,792
- I'M NOT
A LITTLE GIRL ANYMORE!

290
00:12:15,834 --> 00:12:17,792
I CAN AIRBEND
JUST AS WELL AS YOU.

291
00:12:17,834 --> 00:12:20,125
I KNOW EVERYTHING
ABOUT OUR CULTURE AND HISTORY,

292
00:12:20,166 --> 00:12:21,917
AND I HAVE A STRONGER CONNECTION
WITH THE SPIRITS

293
00:12:21,959 --> 00:12:23,333
THAN YOU EVER WILL.

294
00:12:23,375 --> 00:12:27,166
LEAD YOUR OWN CLASS!

295
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:29,166
- IKKI, MEELO, YOU'RE UP.

296
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:31,875
JUST LEAD THEM
THROUGH THE BAGUA CIRCLE.

297
00:12:34,709 --> 00:12:37,417
- LOOK TO YOUR LEFT!
LOOK TO YOUR RIGHT!

298
00:12:37,458 --> 00:12:41,125
ONE OF THOSE PEOPLE WILL NOT
MAKE IT OUT OF HERE ALIVE.

299
00:12:41,166 --> 00:12:45,458
[peaceful music]

300
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,000
- SORRY IF WHAT I SAID
GOT YOU IN TROUBLE

301
00:12:47,041 --> 00:12:48,375
WITH YOUR DAD.

302
00:12:48,417 --> 00:12:50,375
- IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

303
00:12:50,417 --> 00:12:52,542
HE JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT I'M GROWN UP NOW

304
00:12:52,583 --> 00:12:54,333
AND I DON'T NEED HIM
TELLING ME WHAT TO DO

305
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:57,250
LIKE ONE OF HIS RECRUITS.

306
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:59,834
- I KNOW SOMETHING
THAT'LL CHEER YOU UP.

307
00:13:05,125 --> 00:13:07,625
- WHERE DID
ALL THE SPIRITS GO?

308
00:13:07,667 --> 00:13:09,375
- WHERE ARE THE BABIES?

309
00:13:09,417 --> 00:13:12,542
[bang]
- AAH!

310
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,250
- [grunts]

311
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:23,166
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

312
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:25,792
- WHAT ARE THESE KIDS DOING
IN MY CAMP?

313
00:13:25,834 --> 00:13:27,667
- WE CAUGHT THEM
SNEAKING AROUND.

314
00:13:27,709 --> 00:13:30,166
WE THOUGHT THEY MIGHT
TELL SOMEONE WE'RE HERE.

315
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:32,875
- THEY'RE THOSE NEW AIRBENDERS.

316
00:13:32,917 --> 00:13:36,125
MUST BE LIVING
UP AT THE TEMPLE.

317
00:13:36,166 --> 00:13:37,834
HURRY UP AND GATHER
THE REST OF THE GANG,

318
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:39,208
AND LET'S GET OUT OF HERE

319
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:42,125
BEFORE SOMEONE COMES LOOKING
FOR THESE KIDS.

320
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:44,208
WE'LL TAKE THEM
TO BA SING SE

321
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:47,208
WITH THE REST
OF THE FRESH MEAT.

322
00:13:51,083 --> 00:13:54,250
- TATTOOS.
HOW CAN SHE THINK--

323
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:55,750
[sighs]
FOCUS.

324
00:13:55,792 --> 00:13:57,709
BREATHE.
[inhales]

325
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:00,166
BUMI RUINS EVERYTHING.

326
00:14:00,208 --> 00:14:01,959
INHALE.
[inhales]

327
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,208
FOCUS.

328
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,417
- TAKING A LITTLE BREAK
FROM TEACHING?

329
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:08,333
- I FAILED.

330
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:10,208
BUMI QUIT, AND THE REST
OF THE AIRBENDERS

331
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:11,792
WANT TO GO HOME.

332
00:14:11,834 --> 00:14:12,917
CAN'T THEY SEE
THAT I'M TRYING

333
00:14:12,959 --> 00:14:15,041
TO REBUILD
AN ENTIRE CULTURE?

334
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:17,208
- YOU KNOW, JUST BECAUSE
THESE PEOPLE CAN AIRBEND,

335
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:20,041
IT DOESN'T AUTOMATICALLY
MAKE THEM AIR NOMADS.

336
00:14:20,083 --> 00:14:22,375
- TELL ME ABOUT IT.

337
00:14:22,417 --> 00:14:24,041
- I REMEMBER WHEN I MOVED
OUT OF MY PARENTS' HOUSE

338
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:25,917
TO BECOME AN AIR ACOLYTE.

339
00:14:25,959 --> 00:14:28,041
THAT FIRST NIGHT,
I WAS SO SCARED AND LONELY,

340
00:14:28,083 --> 00:14:30,375
AND THE BED WAS SO HARD.

341
00:14:30,417 --> 00:14:33,041
- IT'S ACTUALLY BETTER
FOR YOUR BACK.

342
00:14:33,083 --> 00:14:34,041
SORRY.

343
00:14:34,083 --> 00:14:35,792
- THE POINT IS,

344
00:14:35,834 --> 00:14:37,375
I REALLY WANTED
TO BE THERE,

345
00:14:37,417 --> 00:14:39,208
BUT IT STILL TOOK TIME
FOR ME TO ADJUST

346
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:40,917
AND FEEL LIKE I WAS
A PART OF IT ALL.

347
00:14:40,959 --> 00:14:43,166
THESE PEOPLE ARE PROBABLY
FEELING THE SAME WAY.

348
00:14:43,208 --> 00:14:46,625
YOU HAVE TO BE PATIENT.

349
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:49,083
- NOW I KNOW HOW KORRA FEELS
WHEN I'M TALKING TO HER.

350
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:54,375
THANK YOU, PEMA.

351
00:14:54,417 --> 00:14:57,375
[peaceful music]

352
00:14:57,417 --> 00:15:00,917
♪ ♪

353
00:15:00,959 --> 00:15:04,375
BUMI, I WANT TO APOLOGIZE
FOR LOSING MY PATIENCE.

354
00:15:04,417 --> 00:15:06,542
- I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU.

355
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:07,834
- [squeaks]

356
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:11,667
- HEY, GET BACK HERE!

357
00:15:11,709 --> 00:15:13,166
[sighs]

358
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:14,625
WHERE'S JINORA?

359
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:16,000
- I SAW HER FLY OFF
ON HER GLIDER

360
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,333
WITH HER BOYFRIEND.

361
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:19,500
- WHAT? HER BOYFRIEND?

362
00:15:19,542 --> 00:15:21,750
KAI.

363
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:27,500
- HOW CAN YOU STEAL
THESE BISON?

364
00:15:27,542 --> 00:15:29,333
THEY'RE ENDANGERED.

365
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,291
- THAT'S WHY THEY'RE WORTH
SO MUCH.

366
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:33,125
THE EARTH QUEEN
AND HER FANCY FRIENDS

367
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:36,625
PAY BIG MONEY FOR BISON STEAKS
AND OTHER WEIRD MEAT.

368
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:39,625
I EVEN HEARD SHE ATE
HER DAD'S PET BEAR.

369
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:42,542
- YOU'RE DISGUSTING.

370
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:44,792
[bison whimper]

371
00:15:44,834 --> 00:15:47,959
- HEY, DO THAT SPIRIT BEAMING
THING YOU DID TO FIND ME.

372
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,250
GO TO THE TEMPLE FOR HELP.

373
00:15:49,291 --> 00:15:51,250
- I CAN'T.
I'M ALL CRAMPED IN HERE,

374
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:54,291
AND I NEED QUIET
AND TIME TO FOCUS.

375
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:56,792
BUT MAYBE I CAN SEND
A MESSAGE.

376
00:15:56,834 --> 00:15:59,667
[tense music]

377
00:15:59,709 --> 00:16:03,500
SPIRITS, I NEED YOUR HELP.

378
00:16:03,542 --> 00:16:05,959
- [squeaking]

379
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,709
- GO FIND BUM-JU.
TELL HIM WE'RE IN TROUBLE.

380
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:11,041
- [squeaking]

381
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:12,125
- [squeaks]
- NO, I DON'T THINK

382
00:16:12,166 --> 00:16:14,291
I SHOULD APOLOGIZE.

383
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,750
TENZIN JUST WANTS
TO BOSS EVERYBODY AROUND.

384
00:16:16,792 --> 00:16:18,333
I'M TOO OLD FOR THAT.

385
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:20,750
- [chirping]

386
00:16:20,792 --> 00:16:22,375
- WELL, LET'S FACE IT.

387
00:16:22,417 --> 00:16:25,250
I'M JUST NOT CUT OUT TO BE
AN AIRBENDER.

388
00:16:25,291 --> 00:16:26,542
- [squeaks]

389
00:16:26,583 --> 00:16:28,709
- WELL, THAT'S YOUR OPINION.

390
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:30,792
- [whimpers]

391
00:16:30,834 --> 00:16:33,500
- [squeaking urgently]

392
00:16:33,542 --> 00:16:35,083
- [squeaks]

393
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:39,041
[both squeaking]

394
00:16:39,083 --> 00:16:40,667
- [squeaking urgently]

395
00:16:40,709 --> 00:16:43,709
- WAIT, DID JINORA SEND
THIS SPIRIT?

396
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:45,500
IS SHE IN TROUBLE?

397
00:16:45,542 --> 00:16:48,083
- [squeaks]

398
00:16:48,125 --> 00:16:50,166
- [squeaking]

399
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:52,125
- [whimpering]

400
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:53,500
- JINORA'S IN TROUBLE!

401
00:16:53,542 --> 00:16:54,875
WE HAVE TO GO GET HER.

402
00:16:54,917 --> 00:16:56,166
- HOW DO YOU KNOW?

403
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:57,667
- BUM-JU'S FRIEND TOLD ME.

404
00:16:57,709 --> 00:17:00,000
- YOU ARE ABLE TO COMMUNICATE
WITH THE SPIRITS?

405
00:17:00,041 --> 00:17:02,083
- MORE OR LESS. I GET THE GIST.
LET'S GO!

406
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:04,375
- SHOULDN'T MASTER TENZIN
BE DEALING WITH THIS?

407
00:17:04,417 --> 00:17:06,041
I DON'T WANT
TO GET INTO TROUBLE.

408
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:09,041
- MASTER TENZIN ISN'T HERE.
IT'S UP TO US.

409
00:17:09,083 --> 00:17:10,834
IKKI AND MEELO,
GRAB SOME BISON.

410
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,792
AIRBENDERS, MOVE OUT!

411
00:17:13,834 --> 00:17:15,750
- [squeaks]

412
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:19,834
[bison grunting]

413
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,458
- BISON RUSTLERS.

414
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:29,000
THEY'VE GOT KAI AND JINORA
LOCKED IN CRATES.

415
00:17:29,041 --> 00:17:31,625
LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE GETTING
READY TO LEAVE. WE'LL HAVE TO
MOVE FAST.

416
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:33,458
- I DON'T KNOW IF I'M READY
TO GET IN A FIGHT

417
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,959
WITH SOME BISON RUSTLERS.

418
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,375
I CAN TELL
WITHOUT THE TELESCOPE

419
00:17:36,417 --> 00:17:38,917
THAT THEY'RE MEAN-LOOKING.

420
00:17:38,959 --> 00:17:41,000
- LISTEN, THIS IS WHAT
WE'VE BEEN TRAINING FOR.

421
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:42,375
- WE HAVEN'T BEEN TRAINING
THAT LONG.

422
00:17:42,417 --> 00:17:44,834
- THAT'S NOT IMPORTANT NOW.

423
00:17:44,875 --> 00:17:48,125
REMEMBER HOW WE PERSEVERED
TOGETHER ON THE OBSTACLE COURSE?

424
00:17:48,166 --> 00:17:50,333
- YOU ACTUALLY QUIT.

425
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:53,291
- WELL, I'M NOT QUITTING NOW.

426
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:56,166
I KNOW WE'VE HAD A TOUGH TIME--
ME MORE THAN ANYONE--

427
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:58,291
BUT WE'RE AIRBENDERS,
AND THERE AREN'T MANY OF US,

428
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:00,917
SO WE'VE GOT
TO STICK TOGETHER.

429
00:18:00,959 --> 00:18:03,000
THEY'VE GOT TWO OF OUR OWN
IN CAGES OUT THERE,

430
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:06,375
AND WE'RE NOT LEAVING
UNTIL WE BRING THEM HOME.

431
00:18:06,417 --> 00:18:08,709
- LEAVE NO AIRBENDER BEHIND!

432
00:18:12,917 --> 00:18:15,250
[bison whimpering]

433
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,417
- IN, DOWN, AND...

434
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:20,875
TWIST.

435
00:18:20,917 --> 00:18:24,417
[bison grunts]

436
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:27,208
- FREE THE BISON FIRST.

437
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,000
- HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING OUT?

438
00:18:29,041 --> 00:18:31,792
- [grunts]
- [yells]

439
00:18:31,834 --> 00:18:34,792
[dramatic music]

440
00:18:34,834 --> 00:18:41,792
♪ ♪

441
00:18:41,834 --> 00:18:43,208
- OOF! UGH!

442
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,875
[bang]

443
00:18:47,917 --> 00:18:49,917
[soft music]

444
00:18:49,959 --> 00:18:51,917
- [yells in slow motion]

445
00:18:51,959 --> 00:18:54,709
♪ ♪

446
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,625
- [screams]

447
00:18:56,667 --> 00:18:59,625
[dramatic music]

448
00:18:59,667 --> 00:19:03,917
♪ ♪

449
00:19:03,959 --> 00:19:06,875
- [grunts]

450
00:19:06,917 --> 00:19:08,417
- [groans]

451
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:11,875
- [yells]

452
00:19:11,917 --> 00:19:14,875
- OOH!

453
00:19:14,917 --> 00:19:17,834
[engine revs]

454
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:20,792
- KAI!

455
00:19:26,959 --> 00:19:29,875
[bison bellow]

456
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:36,125
- WHAT'S GOING ON DOWN THERE?

457
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:37,959
- KAI, HELP!

458
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,500
- I'M COMING, JINORA.

459
00:19:40,542 --> 00:19:43,041
[music intensifies]

460
00:19:43,083 --> 00:19:48,917
♪ ♪

461
00:19:48,959 --> 00:19:49,959
- [grunts]

462
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,583
[tires screech]

463
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:59,375
- [grunting]

464
00:19:59,417 --> 00:20:01,500
- WHAT THE--

465
00:20:01,542 --> 00:20:04,458
[bison growling]

466
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,291
[screams]

467
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:14,458
[grunting]

468
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:21,083
YOU GOT ME.

469
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:23,000
I GIVE UP.

470
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:26,000
[yells, grunts]

471
00:20:26,041 --> 00:20:27,625
- YOU THINK
YOU CAN KIDNAP JINORA

472
00:20:27,667 --> 00:20:31,166
AND ALL THESE BABY BISONS?

473
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:33,667
- [groans]

474
00:20:33,709 --> 00:20:36,166
- KAI! THAT'S ENOUGH.
- [groans]

475
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:38,959
- AN AIRBENDER NEVER ATTACKS
A DEFENSELESS OPPONENT.

476
00:20:40,959 --> 00:20:43,583
BUT THAT WAS
VERY GOOD TECHNIQUE.

477
00:20:43,625 --> 00:20:46,583
[peaceful music]

478
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:50,959
♪ ♪

479
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,542
- MAYBE YOU BOYS
HAVEN'T HEARD,

480
00:20:52,583 --> 00:20:55,625
BUT THERE'S SOME NEW AIRBENDERS
AROUND THESE PARTS.

481
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:59,333
AND YOU NEVER MESS
WITH AN AIRBENDER'S BISON.

482
00:21:00,875 --> 00:21:02,500
- WITHOUT MY SHAVED HEAD,

483
00:21:02,542 --> 00:21:03,875
I NEVER COULD HAVE DODGED
THAT NET.

484
00:21:03,917 --> 00:21:05,792
I REALLY FELT IT
COMING AT ME.

485
00:21:05,834 --> 00:21:07,917
YOU GUYS SHOULD TOTALLY
GET SHAVED.

486
00:21:07,959 --> 00:21:10,125
- I'M PROUD OF YOU.

487
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:12,917
YOUR CONNECTION WITH THE SPIRITS
AND NATURAL LEADERSHIP--

488
00:21:12,959 --> 00:21:14,959
YOU REMIND ME OF DAD.

489
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:18,375
- I'M SORRY I'VE BEEN
CAUSING YOU SO MUCH TROUBLE.

490
00:21:18,417 --> 00:21:20,083
I GUESS I WAS JUST SCARED
OF NOT BEING ABLE

491
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:22,667
TO MEASURE UP
AS AN AIRBENDER.

492
00:21:22,709 --> 00:21:24,667
YOU KNOW,
EVEN THOUGH I'M AANG'S SON,

493
00:21:24,709 --> 00:21:28,834
I NEVER REALLY FELT LIKE I WAS
PART OF THE AIR NATION BEFORE.

494
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:32,250
- YOU ARE NOW.

495
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:33,500
[bison snorts]

496
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:36,375
- [laughing]

497
00:21:36,417 --> 00:21:37,709
- THEY'RE SO FRIENDLY NOW.

498
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,917
- THE BISON ARE
THE ORIGINAL AIRBENDERS.

499
00:21:39,959 --> 00:21:44,750
THEY RECOGNIZE
THEIR OWN KIND.

500
00:21:44,792 --> 00:21:46,667
- I'M SORRY FOR RUNNING OFF.

501
00:21:46,709 --> 00:21:48,458
- WE'RE JUST LUCKY
NO ONE WAS HURT.

502
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:51,000
- I KNOW.
- BUT I ALSO REALIZE

503
00:21:51,041 --> 00:21:53,291
THAT PERHAPS I WAS
TOO HARSH WITH YOU.

504
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,917
- DOES THAT MEAN I CAN GET
MY AIRBENDER TATTOOS?

505
00:21:55,959 --> 00:21:57,709
- IT'S HARD FOR ME TO BELIEVE
THAT MY LITTLE GIRL

506
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:00,792
HAS GROWN UP ENOUGH
TO HAVE HER TATTOOS.

507
00:22:00,834 --> 00:22:02,834
BUT I PROMISE
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

508
00:22:02,875 --> 00:22:04,792
FAIR ENOUGH?
- YEAH.

509
00:22:04,834 --> 00:22:06,792
- JINORA, LOOK!
THEY'RE FLYING!

510
00:22:06,834 --> 00:22:08,959
[bison grunting]

511
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:19,208
- I GUESS
EVERYONE IS GROWING UP.
